Jakadan Amurka ya zargi China da 'yan ta'addanci da talla
Mako guda bayan jaridar kasar Sin ta wallafa wani talla mai shafi hudu a jaridar Amurka da ke magana akan amfanin cinikayya tsakanin Amurka da China, jakadan Amurka a China ya zargi Beijing da amfani da jaridar Amurka wajen yada farfaganda.
A ranar Laraba da ta gabata, Shugaba Donald Trump na Amurka ya ambaci kudin da aka biya na jaridar China Daily a cikin jerin sunayen jaridu mafiya yawa a jihar Iowa, bayan da ya zargi China da kokarin tsoma baki a zaben 'yan majalisar dokokin Amurka na ranar 6 ga watan Nuwamba.
Trump ya zargi Beijing da kokarin shiga cikin zaben Amurka, ya nuna abin da jami'an Amurka suka ce Reuters wani sabon mataki ne na kara matsin lamba a kan China.
Yayin da ya zama al'ada ga gwamnatocin kasashen waje su yi tallace-tallace don tallafa wa kasuwanci, Beijing da Washington a halin yanzu suna cikin yakin kasuwanci mai tasowa wanda ya bayyana a matakin shigo da kayayyaki.
An tsara takunkumin da China ta yi a farkon yakin cinikayya don ya shafi masu fitar da kayayyaki a jihohi kamar Iowa, wadanda ke goyon bayan jam'iyyar Republican ta Trump, in ji masana na China da na Amurka.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a China kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa, babban mai fitar da kayayyakin gona zuwa kasar Sin, ya ce Beijing ta cutar da ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da kamfanoni.
Branstad ya rubuta a cikin wata sanarwa a cikin jaridar Des Moines Register ta ranar Lahadi cewa, yanzu haka, China na ninka wannan zalunci ta hanyar buga tallace-tallace na farfaganda a cikin jaridarmu mai 'yanci.
"A cikin yada farfagandarsu, gwamnatin China na amfani da kyawawan al'adun Amurka na 'yancin magana da 'yancin latsawa ta hanyar sanya tallace-tallace masu biya a cikin Des Moines Register", in ji Branstad.
"Ba kamar yadda yake a wani kantin sayar da labarai na titi a Beijing ba, za ka ga 'yan adawa kaɗan kuma ba za ka ga wani ainihin tunani na ra'ayoyin da ba su dace ba da 'yan kasar Sin za su iya yi game da yanayin tattalin arzikin China, saboda kamfanin 'yan jam'iyyar kwaminis ta kasar Sin ne ke mallakar kafofin watsa labarai", ya rubuta.
Ya kara da cewa, "wani babban jaridar kasar Sin ya ki amincewa da buga labarin sa, ko da yake bai bayyana ko wace jarida ce ba".
